# Trivy ignore list — implements ADR-018 §"Vulnerability scanning".
#
# Format: one CVE per line. Every entry MUST include a justification
# AND an expiry date. CI fails the build when an entry is past its
# expiry without renewal.
#
# Example entry shape (uncomment + edit when real entries land):
#
# # CVE-2024-XXXXX
# #   Justification: upstream patch in flight, no exploit path in our
# #     code (we don't call the affected function).
# #   Tracked: https://github.com/celiums/celiums-memory/issues/NNN
# #   Expires: 2026-08-01
# CVE-2024-XXXXX

# (empty for v1 — every known CVE is patched in this release)
